                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310512-93-off548 t18310512-93-crimeloc551"></join>. On the evening of the 6th of May I was in my parlour, from whence I can see into my shop - I saw the prisoner take these two brushes and put them under his coat; he ran off - I and my son pursued him; my son seized him, but he got from him - he then took one of the brushes and threw it at me; I took it up, and still pursued him - I lost sight of him for a short time; he afterwards fell down, and was stopped.</p>
               <p>
            
